Introduction to javascript fetch api 

The Fetch API in JavaScript provides a modern way to fetch resources asynchronously across the network. It's designed to be more flexible and powerful than the older XMLHttpRequest (XHR) approach. Here's a concise introduction to using the Fetch API:



  
  
  
  
fetch.js



fetch('https://api.example.com/data')
  .then(response => {
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error('Network response was not ok');
    }
    return response.json(); // Parse the JSON data
  })
  .then(data => {
    console.log(data); // Process the JSON data
  })
  .catch(error => {
    console.error('Fetch error:', error);
  });
